# NickelHintFix

Fixes two font-rendering problems in Kobo's reader:

- "Wobble": some fonts render letters a pixel too high or low, giving an uneven
  line. NickelHintFix flattens it.
- Vertical (tategaki) CJK text coming out sideways/misplaced (the marks ー 「」 、。)
  when "Better typography" is on. NickelHintFix corrects those pages, and leaves
  horizontal books alone.

Requires firmware 4.21+ (4.x). Does not work on 5.x. See the README for the full
write-up.

## Preferences (KOBOeReader/.adds/nickelhintfix/config)

- nhf_enabled:1            master switch; 0 = behaves as if not installed
- nhf_no_hinting:1         the wobble fix; 0 = stock rendering
- nhf_hinting_allowlist:   comma-separated font families to leave untouched (keep
                           their normal hinting), e.g. Georgia, Kobo Nickel
- nhf_vertfix:1            the vertical-text fix; 0 = off

Changes take effect on reboot.

## Uninstall

Delete KOBOeReader/.adds/nickelhintfix/uninstall and reboot.
